<p>As the eroor states, I am still running an X server…</p>

<p>Solution is…</p>

<p>Hit <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Ctrl + art + f1</code></p>

<p>kill your current X server session by typing <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo Sevice lightdm stop</code> or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo lightdm stop</code></p>

<p>Enter runlevel 3 by typing <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo init 3</code></p>

<p>install <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">bash NVIDA_File*.run</code> file</p>

<p>Check code : <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">lspci | grep -i vga</code></p>

